When adding the blog update the nav to be a 3 column grid
- LOGO + Name (hide on mobile)
- LINKS (home, about, blog)
- ACTIONS (contact, theme)

Will need a mobile menu as well
-->
<nav class="sticky top-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-between bg-neutral-50 bg-opacity-80 p-6 backdrop-blur-md dark:bg-neutral-800 dark:bg-opacity-80">
	<a href="/" class="flex items-center">
		<Logo class="text-slate h-6 w-6" />
		<h2 class="text-slate ml-2 text-2xl font-semibold uppercase leading-none">Brendan Bax</h2>
	</a>
	<div class="flex items-center gap-x-6">
		<a href="/" class="navigation-link">Home</a>
		<a href="/about" class="navigation-link">About</a>
		<a href="/#contact" class="navigation-link">Contact</a>
		<ThemeButton class="mr-6 h-4 w-4" />
	</div>
	<span class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-fg-muted to-transparent opacity-20"></span>
</nav>

<style>
	.navigation-link {
		@apply border-b-2 border-transparent transition-colors hover:border-accent;
	}
</style>
